   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,734:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. The GARCH Model
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.1 What is GARCH?
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GARCH (Generalized Autoregressive Conditional Heteroskedasticity) models the fact that financial markets exhibit 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: volatility clustering
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — periods of high volatility tend to follow high volatility, and calm periods follow calm periods.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Unlike simple historical volatility (which treats all past days equally), GARCH models learn how today
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s volatility
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: depends on:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Yesterday
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s volatility
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (persistence)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Yesterday
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s shock
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (reaction to new information)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.2 Model Specifications
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Two models are fitted and compared:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Symmetric GARCH(1,1)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: σ²_t = ω + α·ε²_{t-1} + β·σ²_{t-1}
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,747:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,748:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: σ²_t
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = conditional variance at time t
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,749:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ω
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,750:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = long-run variance constant (omega)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,751:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: α
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = ARCH coefficient — how much yesterday
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,752:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,753:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s squared shock affects today
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s variance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,755:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: β
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = GARCH coefficient — how much yesterday
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,756:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s variance persists
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,757:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ε_{t-1}
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,758:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = yesterday
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,759:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s return shock (residual)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Constraint:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,760:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  α + β 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 ensures stationarity (variance doesn
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: t explode).
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Asymmetric GJR-GARCH(1,1,1)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: σ²_t = ω + (α + γ·I_{t-1})·ε²_{t-1} + β·σ²_{t-1}
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,764:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: γ
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = leverage parameter — additional variance from negative shocks
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,765:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: I_{t-1}
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,766:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  = indicator function: 1 if ε
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: {t-1} 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,767:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: <
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  0, else 0
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,768:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: This captures the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,769:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leverage effect
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: : stock prices tend to become more volatile after negative returns than after positive
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: returns of the same magnitude.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.3 Innovation Distribution
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Returns are modeled with a 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Student-t distribution
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  rather than Gaussian, because financial returns exhibit:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fat tails
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — extreme moves occur more frequently than a normal distribution predicts
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Excess kurtosis
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — the distribution has heavier tails
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,777:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The degrees-of-freedom parameter (ν) is estimated from data. Lower ν → fatter tails.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,786:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.4 Model Selection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,787:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Both GARCH(1,1) and GJR-GARCH(1,1,1) are fitted, and the model with the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: lower Akaike Information
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,788:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Criterion (AIC)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is selected:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,789:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AIC = 2k - 2·ln(L)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Where k = number of parameters, L = likelihood. AIC penalizes model complexity — GJR-GARCH wins only if the
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,792:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: leverage term significantly improves fit.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,793:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3.5 Configuration
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Parameter | Value | Rationale |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,794:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |-----------|-------|-----------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,795:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,796:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | p (GARCH lag) | 1 | Standard; higher orders rarely
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: improve fit |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,797:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,798:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | q (ARCH lag) | 1 | Captures immediate shock reaction |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,799:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | o (Leverage lag) | 1 | One asymmetric term
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,800:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for leverage effect |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,801:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,802:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Distribution | Student-t | Fat tails in equity returns |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,803:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Return scaling | ×100 | Numerical stability
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,804:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: for optimizer |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,805:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Trading days | 252 | Standard US market annualization |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,806:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. Data Sources 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,807:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Preparation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,808:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.1 Price Data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,809:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Source:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Yahoo Finance API (via 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,810:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: yfinance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,811:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Python library)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,812:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fields:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Open, High, Low, Close, Adjusted Close, Volume
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,813:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,814:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Frequency:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Daily (close-to-close)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,815:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Date range:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,816:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  January 1, 2022 → present (~1,081 trading days)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,817:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Caching:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,818:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  CSV files in 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cache/
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,819:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  directory, 12-hour freshness
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,820:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.2 Returns Computation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Log returns are used for GARCH fitting:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,821:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: r_t = ln(Close_t / Close_{t-1}) × 100
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The ×100 scaling is applied for numerical stability during maximum likelihood estimation. All outputs are de-scaled
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: before use.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,823:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.3 Supplementary Data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Data | Source | Purpose |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,824:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |------|--------|---------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,825:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | VIX (^VIX) | Yahoo Finance | Market fear gauge, regime detection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,826:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | 10Y Treasury (^TNX) | Yahoo Finance | Risk-free rate for Black-Scholes pricing |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,827:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Options chains | Yahoo
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,829:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Finance (live) | Current implied volatility, strike prices, premiums |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4.4 Ticker Universe
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,830:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 42 tickers selected for affordability (stock price $1–$30, enabling ATM straddles within $150):
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: F, SOFI, NIO, RIVN, SNAP, MARA, PLUG, LCID, AMC, GME,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,831:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: BB, CLOV, OPEN, RIOT, SNDL, GEVO, ACHR, RGTI, QUBT, FCEL,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: CHPT, QS, ENVX, RUN, XPEV, UPST, SKLZ, FUBO, CLSK, HIMS,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,832:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: AAL, NCLH, PATH, BLNK, T, INTC, PFE, CCL, PYPL, DKNG,
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: HOOD, SIRI
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,833:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5. Training 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,834:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Model Selection
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.1 Data Splitting
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The system uses a strict 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,835:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: chronological 60/20/20 split
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,836:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  to prevent look-ahead bias:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |←── Train (60%) ──→|←── Val (20%) ──→|←── Test (20%) ──→|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,837:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    Jan 2022              Mid 2024           Late 2025
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:    ~648 days             ~216 days           ~217 days
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,838:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Training set:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,839:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Used to estimate GARCH parameters (ω, α, β, γ, ν)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,840:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Validation set:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Used to verify GARCH forecast correlates with realized vol
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,841:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Test set:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,842:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Completely unseen; used for backtesting trading performance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.2 Fitting Procedure
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,843:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compute log returns from the training set price data
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,844:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Scale returns by ×100 for numerical stability
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,845:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fit GARCH(1,1) via Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,846:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Fit GJR-GARCH(1,1,1) via MLE
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,847:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Select the model with lower AIC
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,848:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Extract conditional volatility series
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  7 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,849:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: De-scale and annualize: 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: σ_annual = (σ_daily / 100) × √252
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,850:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,851:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: arch
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,852:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Python library (by Kevin Sheppard) handles MLE optimization using the SLSQP algorithm with
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: automatic parameter bounds.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,853:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.3 Diagnostics
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After fitting, the system runs:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,854:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,855:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Ljung-Box test
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  on squared standardized residuals (lags 10, 20) — tests whether GARCH has captured
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,856:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: all volatility clustering
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,857:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Jarque-Bera test
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  on residuals — tests normality of standardized residuals
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,858:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Parameter significance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — p-values for all estimated parameters
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,859:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5.4 Validation Metric
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: On the validation set, the system computes the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,860:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Pearson correlation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  between:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,861:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GARCH conditional volatility forecast
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,862:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 5-day rolling realized volatility (from actual returns)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,863:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A correlation > 0.5 indicates the model successfully captures volatility dynamics out-of-sample.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6. Testing 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,864:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Validation
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.1 Backtest Methodology
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,865:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The backtest simulates the exact trading strategy on the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: test set
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,866:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  (final 20% of data, never seen during training):
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Entry rules:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,867:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compute GARCH conditional vol at time t
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,868:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compute 21-day rolling market IV from historical returns
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,869:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Calculate spread = GARCH
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: vol - Market
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,870:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: IV
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,871:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If spread > 2% (entry threshold) → open a long straddle
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Position sizing:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,872:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strike = round(spot price) — ATM
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,873:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Straddle price computed via Black-Scholes
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,874:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Max contracts = floor((capital × 90% - commissions) / straddle
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,875:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: _
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cost)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,876:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Commission: $0.65 per contract per leg
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exit rules:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,877:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hold for exactly 10 trading days
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,878:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Exit value = intrinsic value of call + put at exit spot price
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,879:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: No early exit, no stop loss (hold strategy outperformed stop-loss in testing)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,880:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.2 Performance Metrics
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The backtester computes:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,881:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Metric | Description |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,882:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |--------|-------------|
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,883:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Win Rate | % of trades with positive P
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,884:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,885:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Profit Factor | Gross profits
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: / Gross losses |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,886:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Total Return | (Final capital - Initial) / Initial |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,887:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Max Drawdown | Largest peak-to-trough decline |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,888:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,889:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sharpe Ratio | Risk-adjusted return (annualized) |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,890:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Avg Win / Avg Loss | Mean P
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,891:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L of winning vs losing trades |
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,892:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 6.3 Stop-Loss Comparison
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Two strategies were compared:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,893:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Hold strategy:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,894:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Hold for full 10 days regardless of intraday P
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,895:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: L
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,896:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Stop-loss strategy:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,897:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Close at +10% profit or -5% loss
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,903:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The hold strategy consistently outperformed the stop-loss strategy in backtesting, as stop-losses frequently triggered
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: during normal intraday volatility before the anticipated move occurred. The hold strategy was therefore selected for
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,904:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: production.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,905:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Note:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  For live trading, a +10% take-profit auto-close was added as a practical measure to lock in gains, while no
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,907:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stop-loss is enforced on the downside.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7. Signal Generation 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,908:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Trading Logic
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7.1 Core Signal: IV-RV Spread
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,909:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The fundamental insight is comparing two volatility estimates:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,910:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: GARCH Realized Volatility (RV):
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What the model predicts actual price movements will be
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,911:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Market Implied Volatility (IV):
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  What the options market is pricing in
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,912:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Spread = GARCH_RV - Market_IV
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,913:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If Spread > 0: Options are UNDERPRICED → BUY volatility (long
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: straddle)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,914:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: If Spread < 0: Options are OVERPRICED → SELL volatility
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7.2 Why Long Straddles?
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,915:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: A long straddle profits when the underlying stock moves significantly in 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,916:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: either direction
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,917:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: . It loses when the stock
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stays flat (due to time decay / theta).
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,918:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Straddle P&L = |Stock Move| - Premium Paid - Theta Decay
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: When GARCH predicts higher realized vol than the market expects:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,919:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The stock is likely to move more than priced in
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,920:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The straddle premium is 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,921:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: cheap
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,922:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  relative to expected movement
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,923:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Expected value is positive
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 7.3 Signal Strength
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,924:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Signal strength is computed as the 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: relative spread
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,925:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: :
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,926:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Strength = |Spread| / max(Market_IV, 0.01)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,927:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Signals are ranked by spread (strongest positive spread = best buy-vol opportunity).
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 8. Live Scanning 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,928:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Execution
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 8.1 Scanner Pipeline
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,929:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Every scan cycle:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,930:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Iterate through all 42 tickers
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,931:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: For each ticker:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,932:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: a. Fetch current options chain from Yahoo Finance
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,933:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: b. Find nearest expiration ~14
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,934:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: days out
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: c. Try ATM and ±1 strikes
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,935:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: d. Compute straddle cost (call + put premium × 100 + $1.30
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: commission)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,936:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: e. Filter: must fit within $150 budget
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: f. Fit GARCH model on full price history
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,937:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: g.
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Compute spread = GARCH conditional vol - 21-day rolling realized vol
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,939:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Sort all opportunities by spread (highest first)
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,940:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Return top 8
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 8.2 Execution via Webull
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,941:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Orders are placed through the Webull OpenAPI:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,942:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Authentication:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  HMAC-SHA1 signature on every request
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,943:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2FA:
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Token-based verification via Webull mobile app
   DEBUG: 2026-04-27 23:08:02,944:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
